19/01/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- EU Commissioner for Employment and Social Affairs Anna Diamantopoulou sent a warning letter to the Greek government Saturday (17 January) urging that legislation on employees under contract be harmonised with that of the EU. The letter also notified the government that procedures are underway to refer Greece to the European Court for violating European Community legislation regarding the permanency of state employees under contract. (MPA, ANA - 17/01/04)
